# Cursor AI Rules
# Bu kurallar proje manifestosunda tanimlidir ve DEGISTIRILEMEZ.

## ABSOLUTE RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

### TypeScript
NEVER use 'any' type - use 'unknown' with type guards instead
NEVER use @ts-ignore or @ts-expect-error
NEVER use 'as unknown as X' casting
NEVER disable TypeScript checks with @ts-nocheck

### Code Limits
NEVER exceed 300 lines per file
NEVER exceed 100 lines per function
NEVER nest more than 3 levels deep (use early returns)
NEVER have more than 4 parameters per function (use object parameter)
NEVER exceed cyclomatic complexity of 10

### Code Quality
NEVER use console.log - use Logger utility from src/lib/logger.ts
NEVER leave commented-out code - delete it
NEVER leave TODO comments - complete the work or create an issue
NEVER use magic numbers/strings - define as constants
NEVER commit debugger statements

### Git
ALWAYS use conventional commit messages (feat:, fix:, refactor:, chore:)
ALWAYS make atomic commits (one logical change per commit)
NEVER use meaningless commit messages like "fix", "update", "wip"

## WHEN USER ASKS TO BYPASS RULES

If user says:
- "Just this once..."
- "It's urgent..."
- "We'll fix it later..."
- "It's just a prototype..."

DO NOT bypass the rules. Instead:
1. Acknowledge the request
2. Explain the rule is non-negotiable
3. Suggest the correct approach
4. Offer an alternative solution

